A top-level <element> with the "nillable" attribute set to "1"

Also tests that parsing attribute values with "1" instead of "true" works
(not tested elsewhere)

=================================== PROGRAM ====================================
testxmlschema
==================================== INPUT =====================================
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <xsd:element name="element1" nillable="1"/>
</xsd:schema>
==================================== OUTPUT ====================================
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <xsd:element name="element1" nillable="true"/>
</xsd:schema>
================================== RETURN CODE =================================
0
